<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="252" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d252">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3104</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chairman of the Commission of
                                Neutrals</hi> (<hi rend="italic">White</hi>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-08">May 8, 1933</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Neutral Commission met and I gave the members copies of the circular
                            telegram of the Bolivian Government to its Legations abroad which had
                            been left with me by Mr. Finot on Saturday. I also told them of the
                            conversation I had had on Saturday with the Paraguayan Minister. As a
                            result, it was decided to ask the neighboring countries to meet with us
                            on the following day, Tuesday, May ninth.</p>
                        <closer><signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">rancis</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps">hite</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>